man - an interface to the on-line reference manuals

The table below shows the section numbers of the manual followed by the types of pages they contain.

    1   Executable programs or shell commands / 可執行的程式或是 shell 指令
    2   System calls (functions provided by the kernel) / 系統呼叫（system calls，Linux 核心所提供的函數）
    3   Library calls (functions within program libraries) / 一般函式庫函數
    4   Special files (usually found in /dev) / 特殊檔案（通常位於 /dev）
    5   File formats and conventions eg /etc/passwd / 檔案格式與協定，如 /etc/passwd
    6   Games / 遊戲
    7   Miscellaneous (including macro packages and conventions), e.g. man(7), groff(7) / 雜項（巨集等，如 man(7)、groff(7)）
    8   System administration commands (usually only for root) / 系統管理者指令（通常是管理者 root 專用的）
    9   Kernel routines [Non standard] / Kernel routines（非標準）


man 3 printf            // 3 page
man -k printf           // keyword
man -f smail            // lookup the manual pages referenced by smail
man -aw printf          // list printf all pages


Key
---
space                   next page
page down               next page
page up                 previous page
home                    first page
end                     last page
/string                 forward find 'string'
?string                 backward find 'string'
n,N                     forward next finding, backward next finding
q                       quit

